2. CORE PRINCIPLES

2.1 Incentives Drive Behavior

People and systems follow incentives, not ideals.

PantheonOS treats incentives as vectors, not moral statements.

2.2 Positive-Sum Architecture

Systems flourish when participants gain together.

ZPC (Zero-Positive Converter) is the daemonized embodiment of this principle.

2.3 Resource Flow > Resource Stock

Economies thrive on healthy circulation, not accumulation.

2.4 Information = Currency

Attention, narrative, reputation, clarity ‚Äî all act as currencies.

2.5 Transparency Creates Trust

Mother Duck + Checksum guarantee economic clarity.

2.6 Incentive Geometry

The shape of incentives dictates the shape of behavior.

PantheonOS uses geometry for incentive design:
	‚Ä¢	cones
	‚Ä¢	funnels
	‚Ä¢	lattices
	‚Ä¢	meshes
	‚Ä¢	gradients

2.7 Swarm Dynamics

Large groups follow:
	‚Ä¢	attraction
	‚Ä¢	repulsion
	‚Ä¢	alignment
	‚Ä¢	momentum
	‚Ä¢	pathfinding

PantheonOS designs its economy accordingly.

